Good morning,

This week=E2=80=99s Stratechery Interview is with Tae Kim ( https://x.com/f=
irstadopter ). Kim is a senior technology writer at Barron=E2=80=99s, and h=
as previously written for Bloomberg Opinion and Yahoo Finance. I have read =
and followed Kim, a very astute observer of the technology and gaming indus=
tries, for years.

This week Kim is releasing a new book, The Nvidia Way ( https://wwnorton.co=
m/books/the-nvidia-way ). The Nvidia Way is my favorite kind of tech book: =
it is a history of the company and its founders and all of the decisions th=
ey made decades before Nvidia became the most valuable company in the world=
; it is those decisions that create a culture. For Kim, Nvidia is impossibl=
e to understand without understanding that culture =E2=80=94 that is The Nv=
idia Way =E2=80=94 which, by extension, means understanding CEO Jensen Huan=
g (Huang is referred to within Nvidia and in this interview by his first na=
me).

In this interview we work our way through the book, covering everything fro=
m Nvidia=E2=80=99s focus on software, its organizational structure, how the=
 company regularly invested years ahead market opportunities, and why all o=
f this is downstream from Jensen. What you will come to realize is how much=
 of Nvidia=E2=80=99s sudden success was very much decades in the making, an=
d why Jensen and Nvidia are the true heirs to Steve Jobs and Apple.

